Standalone teacher training institutes, previously outside accreditation frameworks, will now be evaluated under uniform standards. Aligned with NEP 2020, the bill aims to streamline regulation, accreditation, and learning outcomes across universities and colleges, providing consistency and a common benchmark.
title: HECI Bill likely to be introduced next week, standalone teacher training institutes may gain accreditation

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Israel's military announced the targeted killing of senior Hamas commander Raad Saad, a key planner of the October 7th attack. This strike, authorized by Prime Minister Netanyahu, retaliates for recent Israeli troop injuries. Saad, a long-time Hamas operative, held significant roles, including heading operations and weapons manufacturing, and had survived previous assassination attempts.
title: Israel eliminates top Hamas commander; video of targeted strike out

author: AAKASH AHUJA
description: A fatal stabbing in Rudrapur has ignited violent protests, leading to police lathicharge and arson at the roadways bus station. Two men are detained as Hindu organizations express outrage over the death of Tushar Sharma. Authorities are scanning CCTV footage to apprehend more suspects involved in the incident, which police state stems from a long-standing rivalry, not communal tensions.
title: Man fatally stabbed in clash between two groups in Uttarakhand's Khatima; shops set on fire

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The BJP has strongly criticized West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee following chaos at Salt Lake Stadium during Lionel Messi's visit. Leaders accused the state government of gross mismanagement, demanding accountability and punishment for those responsible. The incident saw fans protesting, leading to vandalism and a police baton charge, with many ticket holders unable to see the football star.
title: 'Mere apology not enough’: BJP targets Mamata over chaos at Messi event in Kolkata; demands legal action

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: India has intensified its aid to Sri Lanka following Cyclone Ditwah, deploying an Engineer Task Force to restore critical infrastructure and providing extensive medical support. The Indian Army is working with Sri Lankan counterparts to rebuild damaged bridges, while Operation Sagar Bandhu delivers essential medicines and humanitarian assistance, underscoring India's commitment to its neighbor's recovery.
title: Operation Sagar Bandhu: India boosts connectivity restoration efforts in Sri Lanka; watch

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Kerala's first woman IPS officer, R Sreelekha, has emerged as a potential candidate for the first BJP Mayor of Thiruvananthapuram after the saffron party's historic win. Sreelekha, who recently joined the BJP, secured a significant victory in the Sasthamangalam ward. The party will decide on the mayoral post.
title: Who is R Sreelekha? BJP’s frontrunner for Thiruvananthapuram mayor

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Blake Lively celebrated a business venture amid reports of a strained friendship with Taylor Swift. Swift is reportedly "hurt" and feels used due to Lively's legal issues involving her "It Ends with Us" co-star. Lively's social media post focused on her haircare brand collaboration, pointedly avoiding any mention of Swift, highlighting a careful navigation of public perception and personal relationships.
title: Blake Lively calls Taylor Swift ‘the dreamiest friend’ amid Eras Tour buzz

author: NEEL KAMAL
description: Two young Punjabi students, Gurdeep Singh (27) and Ranveer Singh (18), were tragically shot and killed in Edmonton, Canada, while en route to a party. The victims, both from Mansa district, were reportedly shot while in their car. Canadian police are investigating the incident and have apprehended several Punjabi youths.
title: Canada shooting: 2 Punjabi youths killed while heading to party; probe underway

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: In a delightful turn of the spotlight, iconic figures like Robin Williams and Riteish Deshmukh left their comedic roots behind, captivating audiences with unexpected depth. Meanwhile, Robert Pattinson transformed his 'Twilight' persona, exploring darker, more complex characters, while Alia Bhatt took bold strides into serious narratives, far from her romantic comedies.
title: From Manoj Bajpayee to Robin Williams: 6 actors who played against their public image

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Two American soldiers and a civilian interpreter died in a Syrian ambush. The attack near Palmyra was blamed on an Islamic State gunman. President Trump vowed severe retaliation. Syria's foreign minister condemned the violence. The attacker was killed by partner forces. This marks the first US casualties since the fall of the Assad regime.
title: 'ISIS attack' on US troops: Trump vows 'very serious retaliation' — what we know so far

author: TNN
description: Congress MLA H A Iqbal Hussain predicted Deputy Chief Minister D K Shivakumar will become Chief Minister on January 6 or 9, sparking political speculation. While Hussain strongly supports Shivakumar for the post, Shivakumar himself urged people not to take the MLA's remarks seriously, stating legal action might be necessary.
title: Karnataka power tussle: Congress MLA says DKS will become CM next month

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Lionel Messi's GOAT India Tour 2025 arrives in Mumbai, featuring a padel exhibition at the Cricket Club of India and a seven-a-side exhibition match at Wankhede Stadium. The tour will also include a private charity fashion show with memorabilia from Argentina's 2022 World Cup win.
title: Lionel Messi GOAT India Tour: Complete Mumbai itinerary, timings - check full schedule

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: Atlanta Braves are reportedly exploring a blockbuster trade for Texas Rangers star Corey Seager, a move that could significantly alter the NL playoff landscape. Despite Seager's hefty contract and a no-trade clause, the Braves see him as a crucial solution for their shortstop woes. This potential deal offers Atlanta elite offense and Texas a chance to rebuild their farm system.
title: MLB rumors: Braves eye $325M Rangers superstar in blockbuster trade move

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tragedy struck Brown University as a shooting claimed two lives and injured nine. Hours after the incident, authorities admitted to having no clear leads or suspect in custody, despite an earlier university statement. Questions arose regarding the availability of information and video footage from the classroom where the devastating event unfolded.
title: 'No footage of shooter, gun not identified': Cops admit no leads yet in Brown University shooting

author: NEHA MADAAN
description: Mumbai leads Indian cities in road traffic CO₂ emissions per km due to high vehicle density. A new study reveals major metros like Delhi and Bengaluru also show significant NOx and CO pollution. The research, part of the CHETNA project, mapped emissions across 15 cities at a 500-meter resolution.
title: Mumbai tops road traffic CO2 emissions/km; Delhi & Bengaluru among nation’s top 3 — key findings

author: SOUMITRA BOSE
description: A computer repairman, Vaibhav Agarwal, was arrested as the mastermind of a Rs200 crore MD drug manufacturing racket in Wardha. He learned drug synthesis online and used his familiarity with police routines to operate a clandestine lab near a police station. DRI busted the unit, seizing 128kg of MD and advanced equipment.
title: Rs 200cr drug bust: Wardha MD racket mastermind ran lab 2km from police station; fixed their CCTVs

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Congress is holding a major rally at Ramlila Maidan to protest alleged "vote chori" and issues with electoral rolls. Top leaders, including Rahul Gandhi and Mallikarjun Kharge, will address the gathering. The party claims to have collected over five crore signatures nationwide, criticizing the Election Commission's neutrality and demanding electoral reforms.
title: Congress to hold major rally at Delhi’s Ramlila Maidan — all you need to know

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi-NCR choked under severe toxic smog, with air quality hitting 491, the worst this year. Authorities invoked Stage IV GRAP, banning construction and restricting diesel trucks. Schools and offices adopted hybrid models. Experts cite emissions and weather for the crisis, urging emission cuts. Residents advised to stay indoors.
title: Delhi chokes on ‘severe plus’ AQI: Smog engulfs city, low visibility; key points

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Ranveer Singh's film 'Dhurandhar' is experiencing overwhelming demand, leading to extended showtimes, including midnight and early morning slots in major cities. The action drama, directed by Aditya Dhar, is nearing Rs 300 crore at the box office, with impressive weekend collections and a strong opening day, indicating its potential to surpass 'Padmaavat'.
title: 'Dhurandhar' gets new midnight show times in Mumbai and Pune

author: SANJAY SHARMA
description: Delhi schools hybrid classes 2025: Delhi schools have shifted to hybrid classes for students in Classes 1–9 and 11 as air pollution in the city worsens under GRAP-IV. The Directorate of Education instructed all government, government-aided, unaided private schools, and NDMC, MCD, and Delhi Cantonment Board schools to implement online and in-person learning wherever feasible. Stage IV restrictions include 50% staff work-from-home for offices, bans on BS-III petrol and BS-IV diesel vehicles, and limits on construction and non-essential trucks.
title: GRAP-IV in Delhi: Schools shift to hybrid mode; all you need to know

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Event organiser Satadru Dutta was arrested at Kolkata airport, preventing him from leaving the city after the chaotic Lionel Messi show at Salt Lake Stadium. Thousands of fans were left disappointed by the aborted programme, with allegations of mismanagement surfacing. Police confirmed investigations are underway into the fiasco.
title: Messi event chaos: How event organiser was stopped from fleeing Kolkata; full refunds offered

author: SUBRAT MUKHARJEE
description: In his final match, John Cena faced Gunther in a hard-fought battle. Despite multiple Attitude Adjustments and a leg drop, Cena couldn't secure the win. Gunther ultimately triumphed, forcing Cena to tap out to a sleeper hold, ending the legend's career with a submission loss.
title: WWE Saturday Night’s main event: Gunther defeats John Cena by submission

author: PRITHVIJIT MITRA
description: Lionel Messi's brief 22-minute appearance at Salt Lake stadium ended in chaos as 60,000 disgruntled fans, unable to see the star, erupted in violence. Frustration over poor visibility and absent celebrities led to mayhem, including arson, vandalism, and a police lathi-charge, lasting over an hour.
title: When Messi mania turned messy: Chairs thrown, sofa set on fire — Inside the Kolkata chaos

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Panic gripped Brown University as a mass shooting unfolded during final exams. A chilling text from a student hiding in a closet, detailing the chaos and fear, surfaced online. The attack left at least two dead and eight injured, prompting a massive police response and forcing students to shelter in place amidst intense fear and shock.
title: ‘Am going to run & I love you’: Son updates mother as Brown University shooting unfolds

author: PRIYANGI AGARWAL
description: Delhi faces severe air pollution as AQI crosses 450, triggering Stage IV of the Graded Response Action Plan. Restrictions include a ban on BS III petrol and BS IV diesel vehicles, work-from-home for 50% of office staff, and a halt to construction.  These measures aim to curb pollution and protect public health.
title: Delhi AQI hits 455: GRAP stage III–IV curbs kick in; 50% WFH for offices, hybrid classes for schools

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: Fernando Mendoza has made history, becoming Indiana's first Heisman Trophy winner. The quarterback led the Hoosiers to an undefeated season and Big Ten title with stellar passing numbers. Mendoza's journey from a lightly recruited prospect to college football's pinnacle highlights his dedication and belief, inspiring many with his powerful message.
title: Who is Fernando Mendoza? Meet the first Indiana Hoosier to win the Heisman

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A neurosurgeon reveals Japan's exceptional longevity stems not just from diet, but from daily habits. Consistent routines, mindful eating with smaller portions, integrated physical activity, and strong social connections significantly reduce strain on the nervous system and metabolism. This approach fosters healthier aging, emphasizing preventive care and a balanced lifestyle over quick fixes.
title: Neurosurgeon explains why Japanese people live longer and healthier lives

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: China is reportedly rejecting US-made Nvidia H200 AI chips, favouring domestic alternatives. This move challenges a US strategy to gain market share with less advanced exports. Beijing is also reportedly offering substantial incentives to boost its local chip industry, aiming for greater semiconductor independence and reducing reliance on foreign suppliers.
title: US–China chip rift: White House AI czar flags rejection of US chips; Nvidia blames overbroad export controls

author: P NAVEEN
title: Big cat toll: 6th tiger dies in MP in a week, annual death hits record 54

author: SAIBAL BOSE
description: Football fans in Kolkata were left deeply disappointed and feeling cheated after the much-anticipated Messi event descended into chaos.  Despite paying exorbitant prices for tickets, many struggled to get a glimpse of the superstar due to overwhelming crowds and a lack of proper crowd control.  The situation escalated, leading to frustration and anger among attendees.
title: Inside fan uproar: Rs 16k ticket, but Messi lost among VIPs; ‘what were politicians doing there?’

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Ranveer Singh's espionage thriller 'Dhurandhar' is a massive box office success, nearing Rs. 300 crore in its second week. The film, featuring a stellar cast, has shown consistent growth, with its Day 8 collection surging over 20%. At this trajectory, 'Dhurandhar' is poised to surpass 'Padmaavat' and become Singh's highest-grossing film ever.
title: ‘Dhuranndhar’: Ranveer, Akshaye, Madhavan starrer marches towards Rs 300 cr; to beat Padmaavat

author: SUBHRO NIYOGI
description: Event organizer Satadru Dutta was arrested on Saturday after being deplaned from a chartered flight carrying Lionel Messi and his Inter Miami teammates. Dutta, who had advertised the event, attempted to negotiate with police on the tarmac, offering to refund fans for the cancelled football match. Despite his pleas to continue with the tour, authorities prevented him from leaving Kolkata.
title: Messi tour chaos: Organiser boards plane with football icon, deplaned before take-off; arrested

author: RAKESH PRAKASH
description: A Bengaluru doctor-turned-politician, Dr. Anjali Nimbalkar, saved a passenger's life on an IndiGo flight from Goa to Delhi. The American woman collapsed mid-air with symptoms of a seizure. Dr. Nimbalkar provided immediate medical aid, reviving her. When the passenger collapsed again, a priority landing was arranged in Delhi, ensuring her evacuation to a hospital.
title: Mid-air emergency: Bengaluru doctor revives US passenger; plane makes priority landing in Delhi

author: MURARI SHETYE
description: CBI sleuths are in Thailand to deport Birch by Romeo Lane owners Saurabh and Gaurav Luthra, following a fire that killed 25. The brothers fled after the incident and were detained for illegal stay, with their passports impounded. The nightclub operated illegally for 18 months without necessary permissions and an expired license.
title: Goa fire: CBI team lands in Thailand to bring back Luthra bros; 'duo will return to India next week'
